<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/116.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                                </placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>354. Department’s 287, July 20. Have brought Ghiloni case personally
                            again to attention Minister Foreign Affairs who promises to have matter
                            studied promptly. He seems more favorable than formerly to idea of
                            naturalization.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Page.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>